        public ExternalAnnotator(String name,

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the AnalysisEngine, Leo will make sure it is unique.
        implementation_class - the fully qualified name of the Annotator Class.

      • ExternalAnnotator

        public ExternalAnnotator(String descriptor,
                 boolean byName,
                 NameValue... paramValues)
                  throws IOException,
                         org.apache.uima.util.InvalidXMLException
        Create this annotator by importing an external descriptor.
        Parameters:
        descriptor - path or name of a descriptor file used to generate the AED
        byName - if true then try to import by name otherwise import by location
        paramValues - Optional, list of parameters names and values to set. Creates the parameter if it does not already exist.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the descriptor cannot created.
        org.apache.uima.util.InvalidXMLException - if there is a problem creating the xml.
